{
  "texts": [
    "Analysis of Biases at map level for the Gradient-Order Template MethodThe observed E and B modes with Wiener-filter (for a detailed description, please refer to Section 4.1) are as follows:E = W E (E lens + E noise), B = W E (B lens + B noise), φ = W ϕ (ϕ + ϕ noise),(2.23)with which we calculate the gradient order of the lensing B-modes template according to Section 2.1, following Eq.",
    "(A.3), and get:B temp = B (1) [W E (E lens + E noise) * W ϕ (ϕ + ϕ noise)] = B (1) [W E E lens * W ϕ ϕ] + B (1) [W E E noise * W ϕ ϕ] + B (1) [W E (E lens + E noise) * W ϕ ϕ noise] = B temp S + B temp N.(2.24)Here B (1) [E * ϕ] represents the operation of constructing the gradient order template with E and ϕ.",
    "We have checked that the tensor components have negligible contribution to the constructed lensing B-mode template, i.e.",
    "scalar E-mode is the primary contributor (see Appendix D).",
    "We artificially define the signal part (B temp S) which consists of the signal (the term in the brace), and the noise part (B temp N) introduced during the lensing template construction procedure.Furthermore, since the input E and φ fields are filtered, B temp S is a filtered estimate of the lensing B-modes."
  ]
}